reviews.text:
High quality of food with fair price. Also.....they have clean and dry floor👍.

Recommend lunch dish: Scallion oil， pork chops and eggs served with rice.

*The pork chops is so f**king good. It absorbed the Chinese wine so that u can have the wine flavor. Also the pork is quite fresh. The egg is smooth and I asked the sources of the egg is from Chinese Hubei farm. The size of the Hubei egg is smaller that the usual egg we can buy from the supermarket. HK people treat Hubei egg like the fine red wine.

The one lost star is because they spend to many effort to provide the premium food ingredients but they never telling or marketing to people until I ask😑. This is bad.

They are trying very hard to replicate old school local restaurant vibe and food, by quite frankly succeeding on neither. 

Acceptable tea but food quality is just quite mediocre. They also do not open for dinner.
creative menu but the taste is just okay
食物還可以，但奶茶未夠班，只欠茶葉佩搭比重和份量。努力……
午餐味道一般，早餐 牛肉麵還可以。
